Pat,

This is actually an interesting advantage of JUnit 4&#39;s 
exception-expecting syntax:

@Test(expected=Exception.class)
@Test public void work() {
  doWork();
}

No uncovered lines there.

In general, though, I would think that calls to fail could be safely 
ignored.  For example, another idiom I&#39;ll use is

for (String s : strings)
  if (shouldntBeHere(s))
    fail(s + &quot; shouldn&#39;t be here!&quot;);

Again, if my tests are running, I&#39;d expect fail not to be executed.

    David Saff

